@dr.bansaridavda @drshefalisani spilling facts about onion based oils and shampoos!

⬇️

🧅Onion Hair products for hairfall/hairgrowth- Hyped or Worth it⁉️

✅Watch this video and Save your money💰💵 

✅Onion contains Sulphur, which can be useful only in one type of hairloss called Alopecia areata-(yes the one Will Smith’s wife has!), not all types of hairloss like genetic, nutritional, hormonal etc.

✅Secondly, only a couple of studies have been done on this, that too years ago and with only a handful of participants. No concrete evidence even of this👆

✅Thirdly, the side effects of onion on the scalp- it can be extremely drying and irritating, thus causing hairfall in return, redness, flaking, itching, burning of eyes etc.

✅So, Consult a certified Dermatologist for your hairfall issues to find out the cause first👩‍⚕️🧑‍⚕️ 

✅The video is a collaboration between @traya.health and @whosunilgrover ❤️

•Continuing our ‘Actives’ series:
 🍊𝟮) 𝗩𝗜𝗧𝗔𝗠𝗜𝗡 𝗖🍊

-Numerous benefits and properties of Vitamin- C makes it a ‘must-have’ in my day to day life.

-It is an anti-aging, anti-oxidant, anti-inflammatory, brightening, hydrating wonder molecule.

Q) How often to use?
-Once a day in the morning is ideal.

Q) Effective forms of Vitamin C?
- L-ascorbic acid, Magnesium ascorbyl phosphate, Sodium ascorbyl phosphate, Tetreahexyldecyl ascorbate. 
-Serums are more affective than creams and toners.

Q) How much percentage Vitamin-C to start with?
- Start slow with 5% ,then can gradually increase upto 20%.
-Do a patch test on neck or forearm before applying on face.

Q) What to follow it up with?
- A Moisturiser to lock the goodness of Vitamin C (optional).
-Sunscreen to prevent oxidation of Vitamin C is a must.

Q) How long it takes for Vitamin C to work?
- 4-12 weeks , depending on formulation, concentration and consistency in application!

Q) What other actives Vitamin C pairs well with?
- Azelaic acid, Niacinamide, Vitamin E, Kojic acid, Hyaluronic acid.

-You can start using Vitamin C from your 20’s..I say go for it!

Happy Skincare✨

•Starting my series of breakdown of ‘Actives’, here is the first one :- 
 🌾𝗔𝗭𝗘𝗟𝗔𝗜𝗖 𝗔𝗖𝗜𝗗🌾

1)What is it?
-Naturally occurring acid found in grains like rye, barley and wheat.

2)What are the benefits?
-It helps the skin renew itself,reduces hyperpigmentation and has antioxidant, anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties.

-It's effective in treating skin conditions like Post inflammatory erythema, Acne, Rosacea.

-Suitable for all skin types,especially oily and sensitive skins.

3)Which other actives pair well with it?
- Almost all like Vitamin C, niacinamide, salicylic acid,glycolic acid, mandelic acid..

4)How often to use?
-Once or twice daily.

-I layer it on with my Vitamin C serum once daily.

5)How soon will you see results?
- 6-8 weeks minimum it takes to show results..be consistent in daily application.

Happy Skincare ✨
